IP Addressing and Netwroking Basics:

What is an IP Address?
- A unique identifier assigned to each device on a network.
- Works like a home address- used to send/receive data.
- Most common type: IPv4 (ex. 192.168.0.1)
- IPv4 = 4 octets(32 bits) = values between 0 -255 per octet
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Network vs Brodcast Address:
- 192.168.1.0 = Network address
- 192.168.1.255 = Broadcast address
- Used to target all devices on the network
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Find your IP Address:
- Windows: ipconfig
- Linux/macOS: ifconfig or ip a s

Example output:
IP: 192.168.66.89
Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.0 or /24
Broadcast: 192.168.66.255
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Subnet Mask:
- Used to seperate network and host parts of the address
- /24 = 255.255.255.0 - 256 IPs (254 usable)
- /24 means first 3 Octets are fixed
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Private vs Public IPs
Private IP Ranges:
- 10.0.0.0 - 10.255.255.255 (10/8)
- 172.16.0.0 -172.31.255.255
- 192.168.0.0 - 192.168.255.255
Private = internal network only
Public = accessible over the internet
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Routers and Routing:
- A router acts like a post office
- It forwards packets between networks
- Works at OSI Layer #
- Reads the destination IP address and picks the next best hop


